title: PML-Q’ Ch Salik Hussain wins NA-64 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League (PML-Q) Candidate Ch Salik Hussain has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-64 Gujrat-III by securing 1,05205 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent candidate Qaisera Ilahi, who bagged 80,946 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 40 percent.
